iversity}}\n* {{cite book|author=Army History Directorate (Greece)|title=A concise history of the Balkan Wars, 1912\u20131913|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=n4-RAAAAIAAJ|year=1998|publisher=Army History Directorate|isbn=978-960-7897-07-7}}\n* Stavrianos, L.S. '' The Balkans Since 1453'' (1958), major scholarly history; [https://archive.org/details/balkanssince145300lsst online free to borrow]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Balkan Wars}}\n*[https://www.mtholyoke.edu/acad/intrel/boshtml/bos143.htm U.S. State Department. \"The Formation of the Balkan Alliance of 1912\" (1918)]\n* C. Hall, Richard: [https://encyclopedia.1914-1918-online.net/article/balkan_wars_1912-1913/ Balkan Wars 1912\u20131913], in: [https://encyclopedia.1914-1918-online.net/home.html/ 1914-1918-online. International Encyclopedia of the First World War].\n*[http://www.gutenberg.org/files/11676/11676.txt Project Gutenberg's The Balkan Wars: 1912\u20131913, by Jacob Gould Schurman]\n*[http://countrystudies.us/bulgaria/12.htm US Library of Congress in the Balkan Wars]\n*[http://cnparm.home.texas.net/Wars/BalkanCrises/BalkanCrises00.htm The Balkan crises, 1903\u20131914].]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20081231100539/http://www.turkeyswar.com/prelude/balkanwars1.htm Balkan Wars from a Turkish perspective]\n*[[Wikisource]]: [[:s:The New Student's Reference Work/The Balkans and the Peace of Europe|The New Student's Reference Work/The Balkans and the Peace of Europe]]\n*[http://www.europeanfilmgateway.eu/node/33/efg1914%20balkan%20war/multilingual:1/showOnly:video Historic films about the Balkan Wars at europeanfilmgateway.eu]\n\n{{Balkan Wars}}\n{{Great power diplomacy}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Balkan Wars| ]]\n[[Category:Causes of World War I]]\n[[Category:1910s in Europe]]\n", "text_old": "{{Hatnote|For the articles examining each war individually, see [[First Balkan War]] and [[Second Balkan War]]. For the 1990s conflicts in the region, see [[Yugoslav Wars]].}}\n{{Short description|Two wars on Balkan Peninsula 1912\u20131913, leading to the Balkan Crisis of 1914 and start of WWI}}\n{{More citations needed|date=February 2019}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n| conflict    = Balkan Wars\n| partof=\n| image       = Balkanska-voina2.jpg\n| caption     = Bulgarian soldiers charging the Turkish defenses in the [[Battle of Kirk Kilisse]]\n| date        = 8 October 1912 \u2013 18 July 1913<br/>({{age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=10|day1=08|year1=1912|month2=07|day2=18|year2=1913}})<br/>'''First Balkan War:'''<br>8 October 1912 \u2013 30 May 1913<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=10|day1=08|year1=1912|month2=05|day2=30|year2=1913}})<br>'''Second Balkan War:'''<br>29 June \u2013  10 August 1913<br>({{Age in months, weeks and days|month1=06|day1=29|year1=1913|month2=8|day2=10|year2=1913}})\n| place       = {{hlist |[[Adrianople Vilayet|Adrianople]]\n |[[Scutari Vilayet|Scutari]]\n |[[Kosovo Vilayet|Kosovo]]\n |[[Monastir Vilayet|Manastir]]\n |[[Salonica Vilayet|Salonica provinces]]\n |[[Aegean Islands]]\n |[[Aegean Sea]]}}\n| territory=\n| result      = {{Collapsible list|title='''First Balkan War:'''|titlestyle=font-weight:normal;background:transparent;text-align:left;|\n* Balkan League victory \n* [[Treaty of London, 1913|Treaty of London]]\n}}\n{{Collapsible list|title='''Second Balkan War:'''|titlestyle=font-weight:normal;background:transparent;text-align:left;|\n* [[Treaty of Bucharest, 1913|Treaty of Bucharest]] \n* [[Treaty of Constantinople (1913)|Treaty of Constantinople]]\n}}\n| status=\n| combatants_header=\n| combatant1  = {{Collapsible list|title='''[[First Balkan War]]'''|titlestyle=font-weight:normal;background:transparent;text-align:left;|{{flag|Ottoman Empire}}\n<br/>'''Support:'''<br/>\n{{Flag|Austria-Hungary}}\n}}\n| combatant1a = {{Collapsible list|title='''[[Second Balkan War]]'''|titlestyle=font-weight:normal;background:transparent;text-alig